eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli has the details. #eNCA #DStv403  DURBAN - Communities across Durban are dealing with the after-effects of the floods. Many are still without basic services. Residents of Tongaat took their frustrations out by blocking the roads and protesting not having water for over 50 days. They are accusing the government of poor service delivery and neglect. eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli has the details in the video above.